  "prompt": "What are the best 5 things I can do with my first salary?",
  "response": "Congratulations on your first salary! Here are five practical and meaningful things you can do to make the most of it:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Save and Invest**\n   - Start building an emergency fund by saving at least 10-20% of your salary. This will provide a safety net for unexpected expenses.\n   - Consider opening a fixed deposit (FD) or exploring low-risk investment options like mutual funds or SIPs to grow your money over time.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Treat Yourself**\n   - Celebrate your hard work by treating yourself to something you\u2019ve been wanting, like a small purchase, a nice meal, or an experience that brings you joy. It\u2019s a way to acknowledge your achievement.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Pay Off Debts (If Any)**\n   - If you have any outstanding debts or loans, prioritize paying them off. Clearing debt early can save you money on interest and give you financial peace of mind.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Give Back**\n   - Consider sharing your success with others. You could gift something to your family, donate to a cause you care about, or simply treat your loved ones to a meal or experience.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Plan for the Future**\n   - Start budgeting for future goals, such as travel, higher education, or personal development. You could also begin saving for larger expenses like a car or a home.\n\n---\n\nRemember, financial discipline early in your career will set you up for long-term success. Enjoy your first salary responsibly! \ud83d\ude0a",
  "temperature": 1.0,
